===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
Multiple theories:
* He Linyi ({{lang|zh|何琳儀}}): {{liushu|i}}: a spear {{zh-l|*𫲸}} (now {{zh-l|*𥎆}}) + a distinguishing mark {{lang|zh|口}}.<ref name="說文新證">季旭昇，2004《說文新證》，台北：藝文印書館印行，2014年9月第二版。p.601-602</ref><ref name="漢多">[https://humanum.arts.cuhk.edu.hk/Lexis/lexi-mf/search.php?word=%E5%AE%B3 漢語多功能字庫 - 字頭 「害」]</ref>
* {{zh-ref|Li Xueqin (2012)}}: {{liushu|psc}}. The phonetic component is {{zh-l|𡩜|xiàn}}.<ref>李學勤，2012《字源》，天津：天津古籍出版社，2013年7月2次印刷。p.662</ref>
*  Guo Moruo ({{lang|zh|郭沫若}}),<ref name="說文新證"></ref> Dai Jiaxiang ({{lang|zh|戴家祥}})<ref name="漢多"></ref>: {{liushu|p}}, ancient form of {{zh-l|*蓋}} ("lid; cover"). 
* Gao Hongying ({{lang|zh|高鴻纓}}): {{liushu|j}}, original character of {{zh-l|*桷}}, borrowed for sound, which was a {{liushu|p|nocap=yes}} of a house's [[rafter#Etymology_1|rafters]] (see {{zh-l|*舍}}).<ref name="說文新證"></ref>
* Chen Bingxin ({{lang|zh|陳秉新}}): Original form of {{zh-l|*𠤳}}, written as  {{lang|zh|⿷𠥓⿴害五}} in bronze inscriptions, which itself is an ancient way of writing the {{zh-l|*胡}} in {{lang|zh|{{w|㝬簋|胡簋|lang=zh}}}}.<ref name="說文新證"></ref><ref name="漢多"></ref>
* {{w|Shuowen Jiezi}}: {{Han compound|宀|口|丯|ls=psc|c1=s|c2=s|c3=p}}.

